items.description: Color scheme based on the color pastel of MDR division in Severance Apple+ TV show

items.name: ttwnty.vim
items.description: ttwnty.vim is a minimal vim color scheme based on your terminal colors

items.name: mine-pine
items.description: Neovim color scheme - based on [rose-pine](https://github.com/rose-pine/neovim) but warmer, more cozy, relaxing and easier on eyes :)

items.name: fansi2
items.description: A Neovim color scheme for `notermguicolors` and `termguicolors`. It's like gruvbox but with more blueish hues.

items.name: miasma.nvim-transparent
items.description: a fog descends upon your editor ☁  dark color scheme inspired by the woods for vim and neovim

items.name: vim-lucario
items.description: A Vim / NeoVim plugin manager friendly version of Lucario color scheme. Adding support for Vundle, Pathogen, and vim-plug.

items.name: glacium.nvim
items.description: glacium.nvim: A crisp and calm dual-theme Neovim color scheme inspired by arctic blues, layered oceans, and glacial light

items.name: my-nvim-setup
items.description: My neovim setup. Mix between multiple other people's setups + additional plug ins such as Discord presence, color schemes and more.

items.name: colors-to-config
items.description: A GUI based web app designed to help create color scheme config files for various applications and tools, including tmux, vim/neovim, zsh, and more! Color pickers and live previews help promote experimentation and allows for easy user customization.

items.name: exmachina.vim
items.description: A Star Wars-inspired deep space tech color scheme for Vim/Neovim with integrated airline theme. Features high-contrast cyans and deep blues reminiscent of advanced starship displays.

items.name: springtime-girls
items.description: A light, pastel color scheme for Vim that brings a refreshing and vibrant look to your editor. Inspired by the gentle hues of spring, this theme offers a pleasant visual experience with soft colors that are easy on the eyes.

items.name: zerone
items.description: Zerone is a minimalist black and white color scheme for Neovim, designed for a stylish and sleek coding experience. It is easy on the eyes, making it perfect for long coding sessions or working in low-light environments.
